Title: 1. 2001: A Space Odyssey
description: When a mysterious artifact is uncovered on the Moon, a spacecraft manned by two humans and one supercomputer is sent to Jupiter to find its origins.

Title: 2. Funny Girl
description: The life of Fanny Brice, famed comedienne and entertainer of the early 1900s: her rise to fame as a Ziegfeld Girl, her subsequent career, and her personal life, particularly her relationship with Nick Arnstein.

Title: 3. The Odd Couple
description: A New Yorker newly separated from his wife moves in with his best friend, a divorced sportswriter, but their ideas of housekeeping and lifestyles are as different as night and day.

Title: 4. Planet of the Apes
description: After being kept in hypersleep during a long expedition into deep space, an astronaut crew crash-lands in the 40th century on a planet where highly intelligent non-human ape species are dominant and humans are enslaved.

Title: 5. Hang 'Em High
description: When an innocent man barely survives a lynching, he returns as a lawman determined to bring the vigilantes to justice.

Title: 6. Chitty Chitty Bang Bang
description: A down-on-his-luck inventor turns a broken-down Grand Prix car into a fancy vehicle for his children, and then they go off on a magical fantasy adventure to save their grandfather in a far-off land.

Title: 7. Where Eagles Dare
description: Allied agents stage a daring raid on a castle where the Nazis are holding American brigadier general George Carnaby prisoner, but that's not all that's really going on.

Title: 8. Once Upon a Time in the West
description: A mysterious stranger with a harmonica joins forces with a notorious desperado to protect a beautiful widow from a ruthless assassin working for the railroad.

Title: 9. Coogan's Bluff
description: Arizona Deputy Sheriff Coogan is sent to New York City to escort an escaped fugitive back for trial.

Title: 10. Yellow Submarine
description: The Beatles agree to accompany Captain Fred in his yellow submarine and go to Pepperland to free it from the music-hating Blue Meanies.

Title: 11. Bullitt
description: A nonconformist San Francisco cop is determined to find the underworld kingpin who killed the witness under his protection.

Title: 12. Journey to Shiloh
description: At the beginning of the Civil War, seven friends embark on a cross-country journey in order to join the Confederate army.

Title: 13. Night of the Living Dead
description: A ragtag group of Pennsylvanians barricade themselves in an old farmhouse to remain safe from a horde of flesh-eating ghouls that are ravaging the Northeast of the United States.

Title: 14. I Love You, I Love You
description: After attempting suicide, Claude is recruited for a time travel experiment, but, when the machine goes haywire, he may be trapped hurtling through his memories.

Title: 15. The Great Silence
description: A mute gunfighter defends a young widow and a group of outlaws against a gang of bounty killers in the winter of 1898, and a grim, tense struggle unfolds.

Title: 16. The Queen
description: The behind the scenes of a national drag queen contest in New York City, including the rehearsals leading up to the contest, the conversations in the dressing room and the jealousies that emerge before and after the competition.

Title: 17. The Bride Wore Black
description: Julie Kohler is prevented from suicide by her mother. She leaves the town. She will track down, charm and kill five men who do not know her. What is her goal? What is her purpose?

Title: 18. Memories of Underdevelopment
description: A Cuban man cycles through his opinions and memories as the threat of foreign invasion intensifies and the rest of his family moves to Miami.

Title: 19. The Lion in Winter
description: 1183 A.D.: King Henry II's three sons all want to inherit the throne, but he won't commit to a choice. When he allows his imprisoned wife Eleanor of Aquitaine out for a Christmas visit, they all variously plot to force him into a decision.

Title: 20. The Chronicle of Anna Magdalena Bach
description: The life and music of Johann Sebastian Bach as presented by his wife, Anna.

Title: 21. Stolen Kisses
description: After being discharged from the army, Antoine Doinel centers a screwball comedy where he applies for different jobs and tries to make sense of his relationships with women.

Title: 22. Rosemary's Baby
description: A young couple trying for a baby moves into an aging, ornate apartment building on Central Park West, where they find themselves surrounded by peculiar neighbors.

Title: 23. Romeo and Juliet
description: When two young members of feuding families meet, forbidden love ensues.

Title: 24. Finian's Rainbow
description: An Irish immigrant and his daughter move into a town in the American South with a magical piece of gold that will change people's lives, including a struggling farmer and African American citizens threatened by a bigoted politician.

Title: 25. They Came to Rob Las Vegas
description: A casino blackjack dealer plots with his girlfriend and a group of criminals to hijack and rob an armored car carrying a $7 million in cash while it's in route between Las Vegas and Los Angeles.

Title: 26. Barbarella
description: In the 41st century, an astronaut seeks to stop an evil scientist who threatens to unleash a powerful weapon upon the galaxy, partaking in sexy misadventures along the way.

Title: 27. The Swimmer
description: A man spends a summer day swimming home via all the pools in his quiet suburban neighborhood.

Title: 28. Vixen!
description: The free-spirited wife of a Canadian bush pilot seduces a Mountie, a married couple and her biker brother, all while antagonizing her sibling's draft-dodging black friend.

Title: 29. Oliver!
description: After being sold to the mortician Sowerberry, young orphan Oliver Twist runs away and meets a group of boys trained to be pickpockets by their elderly mentor Fagin in 1830s London in this musical based on Charles Dickens' Oliver Twist.

Title: 30. The Thomas Crown Affair
description: A debonair, adventuresome bank executive believes he has pulled off the perfect multi-million dollar heist, only to match wits with an insurance investigator who will do anything to get her man.

Title: 31. Where Angels Go Trouble Follows!
description: An old-line Mother Superior is challenged by a modern young nun when they take the girls of St. Francis Academy on a bus trip across the United States.

Title: 32. The Big Switch
description: Playboy John Carter is implicated in the murder of a blonde from a discotheque and is forced by gangsters into posing for pornographic photographs.

Title: 33. Candy
description: Candy Christian, an innocent high-schooler, encounters numerous colorful characters and humorous sexual situations while attempting to find meaning in life.

Title: 34. A Fine Pair
description: A detective gets involved with the beautiful daughter of an old friend. The daughter turns out to be a jewel thief, who in turn gets the detective involved in a caper in Austria.

Title: 35. Carne
description: A worker in a meat-packing factory becomes the girl of strangers. After she makes love to her boyfriend, she is raped by a fellow worker.

Title: 36. Yours, Mine and Ours
description: A widower with ten children falls for a widow with eight, and they must decide about forming a huge, unconventional family.

Title: 37. The Wrecking Crew
description: Gold bullion worth USD 1 billion has been stolen from a hijacked train in Denmark. The main suspect is Count Massimo Contini. The US government sends Matt Helm, one of its top agents, to investigate and recover the gold.

Title: 38. The Party
description: A clerical mistake results in a bumbling Indian film star being invited to an exclusive Hollywood party instead of being fired.

Title: 39. Teorema
description: A mysterious young man seduces each member of a bourgeois family. When he suddenly leaves, how will their lives change?

Title: 40. The Green Berets
description: Col. Mike Kirby picks two teams of crack Green Berets for a mission in South Vietnam. First off is to build and control a camp that is trying to be taken by the enemy. The second mission is to kidnap a North Vietnamese General.

Title: 41. Hour of the Wolf
description: While vacationing on a remote German island with his younger pregnant wife, an artist has an emotional breakdown while confronting his repressed desires.

Title: 42. Targets
description: An aging horror star contemplates retirement amid the modern culture of random violence, while a disturbed young gun collector embarks on an unprovoked killing spree.

Title: 43. Spirits of the Dead
description: A trio of Edgar Allan Poe adaptations about a cruel countess haunted by her cousin's stallion, a sadistic soldier haunted by his doppelgänger, and an alcoholic actor haunted by the Devil.

Title: 44. If....
description: In this allegorical story, a revolution led by pupil Mick Travis takes place at an old established private school in England.

Title: 45. Ice Station Zebra
description: USN nuclear sub USS Tigerfish must rush to the North Pole to rescue the staff of Drift Ice Station Zebra weather station.

Title: 46. Hellfighters
description: Divorced Chance Buckman fights international oil rig fires. An injury brings his daughter and to his dismay, she weds Greg, a team member. Chance gets a desk-job, so he and Madelyn remarry, but a Venezuelan oil rig fire reunites them.

Title: 47. Charly
description: An intellectually disabled man undergoes an experiment that gives him the intelligence of a genius.

Title: 48. The Devil Rides Out
description: Devil worshipers plan to convert two new victims.

Title: 49. A Midsummer Night's Dream
description: The adventures of four young lovers, a group of amateur actors and their interactions with fairies come to light in a moonlit forest.

Title: 50. Danger: Diabolik
description: A master thief and his sensual lover pull off heist after heist, all while an envious coalition of cops and gangsters is gunning for them.

Title: 51. Head
description: The Monkees frolic their way through a series of musical set pieces and vignettes containing surreal humor and anti-establishment social commentary.

Title: 52. The Devil's Brigade
description: A US Army lieutenant colonel is tasked with forming an elite commando-style unit from crack Canadian troops and the dregs of the US Army.

Title: 53. The Girl on a Motorcycle
description: A married woman leaves her husband and zooms off on her motorcycle to see her lover.

Title: 54. Firecreek
description: A peace-loving, part-time Sheriff in the small town of Firecreek must take a stand when a gang of vicious outlaws takes over his town.

Title: 55. The Charge of the Light Brigade
description: In 1854, during the Crimean War, poor planning leads to the British Light Brigade openly charging a Russian artillery position with tragic consequences.

Title: 56. The Shoes of the Fisherman
description: After spending decades in a Siberian Gulag labor camp, Roman Catholic priest Kiril Lakota is set free by Russian leader Piotr Ilyich Kamenev at the height of the Cold War.

Title: 57. A Quiet Place in the Country
description: After moving into a dilapidated rural villa to reinvigorate his creative energies, a neurotic artist becomes obsessed with an uninhibited countess who died there many years prior.

Title: 58. The Bat Woman
description: Batwoman is called to investigate a whacked-out scientist who is capturing wrestlers and using their spinal fluid to create a Gill Man.

Title: 59. The Split
description: Thieves fall out when over a half million dollars goes missing after the daring and carefully planned robbery of the Los Angeles Coliseum during a football game, each one accusing the other of having the money.

Title: 60. Carry on Up the Khyber
description: Sir Sidney Ruff-Diamond looks after the British outpost near the Khyber Pass. Protected by the kilted Third Foot and Mouth regiment, you would think they were safe but the Khazi of Kalabar has other ideas.

Title: 61. Hot Spur
description: A deranged stablehand kidnaps the wife of a ranch owner to avenge the rape of his sister.

Title: 62. Blackbeard's Ghost
description: Track coach Steve Walker accidentally invokes the spirit of notorious pirate Captain Blackbeard who was believed dead. He must now lay the pirate to rest and save a local hotel from mobster Silky Seymour, who wants to build a casino.

Title: 63. Witchfinder General
description: During the English Civil War, a young Roundhead seeks vengeance against a vicious witch-hunter and his henchman, who have terrorized the soldier's fiancée and wrongfully executed her uncle.

Title: 64. Shogun's Joy of Torture
description: Three tales of punishment and torture set in Japan in the Middle Ages.

Title: 65. The Heart Is a Lonely Hunter
description: When deaf-mute Singer moves to a new town to be near his hospitalized friend, he makes an indelible impression on the lives of those around him.

Title: 66. Greetings
description: Three friends in New York City discuss how to dodge the draft and Vietnam, JFK's assassination, voyeurism, computer dating, and everything else.

Title: 67. The Scalphunters
description: Forced to trade his valuable furs for a well-educated escaped slave, a rugged trapper vows to recover the pelts from the Indians and later the renegades that killed them.

Title: 68. Day of the Evil Gun
description: A woman and two children are kidnapped by Apaches. The husband of the captured woman enlists the help of his neighbor to find the Apaches that seized his family; not knowing his neighbor has unknown reasons of his own for helping him.

Title: 69. The Lost Continent
description: The captain, crew, and passengers of an old freighter-all of them with dark secrets to keep-find themselves adrift in a mysterious land full of monsters, conquistadors, and killer seaweed.

Title: 70. Rachel, Rachel
description: Rachel is a lonely school teacher who lives with her mother. When a man from the big city asks her out, she starts thinking about where she wants her life to go.

Title: 71. Farewell, Friend
description: After an overseas deployment, two former French Foreign Legion members plan to break into the vault of a French corporation.

Title: 72. The Boston Strangler
description: A series of strangulation murders of Boston women sparks a protracted complex manhunt. Law professor John Bottomley leads a multi-jurisdictional task force in the investigation, with help from surviving victim Diane Cluny.

Title: 73. All the Sins of Sodom
description: Photographer Henning works on erotic images with model. Progress disrupted when mysterious woman seduces one of his models, creating tension and complications in Henning's professional endeavors.

Title: 74. Black Cat
description: Two women are raped and killed by samurai soldiers. Soon they reappear as vengeful ghosts who seduce and brutally murder the passing samurai.

Title: 75. The Stalking Moon
description: U.S. Army soldiers round up a group of Apache, mostly women and children. Surprisingly, they find among them a white woman and her half-Apache son.

Title: 76. Shame
description: In the midst of a civil war, former violinists Jan and Eva Rosenberg, who have a tempestuous marriage, run a farm on a rural island. In spite of their best efforts to escape their homeland, the war impinges on every aspect of their lives.

Title: 77. Lady in Cement
description: During an ocean dive, Miami gumshoe Tony Rome (Frank Sinatra) finds a woman's body with her feet encased in a concrete block and sets out to solve the murder case.

Title: 78. Faces
description: A middle-aged man leaves his wife for another woman. Shortly after, his ex-wife also begins a relationship with a younger partner. The film follows their struggles to find love amongst each other.

Title: 79. With Six You Get Eggroll
description: Two widowed people fall in love and marry, unprepared for the hostile reactions of their children.

Title: 80. Buona Sera, Mrs. Campbell
description: Carla Campbell receives maintenance payment from three former soldiers who all believe themselves to be the father of her daughter, Gia.

Title: 81. The Mercenary
description: A greedy Polish mercenary helps a mine worker and a peasant girl lead a revolution against the Mexican Government, all while being pursued by an American rival.

Title: 82. Krakatoa: East of Java
description: In 1883, ship captain Hanson plans a shipwreck salvage mission in The Dutch East Indies to retrieve a cargo of pearls but an unexpected volcano eruption and a state-ordered transport of convicts upset his plans.

Title: 83. Twisted Nerve
description: A troubled man becomes infatuated with a beautiful young woman and uses a childlike alter-ego to get close to her.

Title: 84. The Magus
description: A teacher on a Greek island becomes involved in bizarre mind games with the island's magus (magician) and a beautiful young woman.

Title: 85. Skidoo
description: A retired gangster must return to work when mob boss God kidnaps his daughter Darlene to force him into killing rival Blue Chips Packard.

Title: 86. The One and Only, Genuine, Original Family Band
description: The eleven members of the Bower family move to Dakota Territory.

Title: 87. Isadora
description: A biography of the 1920s dancer Isadora Duncan, who forever changed people's ideas of ballet. Her nude, semi-nude, and pro-Soviet dance projects as well as her attitude and lifestyle shocked the public of her time.

Title: 88. Dracula Has Risen from the Grave
description: After a Monsignor accidentally brings Count Dracula back from the dead while exorcising his castle, the vampire preys on the holy man's beautiful niece and her friends.

Title: 89. Hell in the Pacific
description: During World War II, an American pilot and a marooned Japanese navy captain are deserted on a small uninhabited island in the Pacific Ocean. There, they must cease their hostility and cooperate if they want to survive, but will they?

Title: 90. Destroy All Monsters
description: In 1999, a race of she-aliens, the Kilaaks, brainwash Earth's monsters into attacking major cities, prompting a team of astronauts to stop the invaders while the monsters battle Ghidorah.

Title: 91. Live a Little, Love a Little
description: Photographer Greg Nolan moonlights in two full-time jobs to pay the rent, but has trouble finding time to do them both without his bosses finding out.

Title: 92. Even the Wind Is Afraid
description: Girls that were punished to sat at a boarding school during Spring Break have no idea the school is haunted by the restless spirit of a former student seeking revenge.

Title: 93. Inga
description: Inga, a 17 year-old, is sent to live with a scheming aunt who wants her to become mistress of her rich neighbour. She falls for a common young man instead.

Title: 94. I Love You, Alice B. Toklas!
description: A thirty-something square falls in love with a hippie and decides to "drop out" himself.

Title: 95. How to Save a Marriage and Ruin Your Life
description: When carefree bachelor David Sloane tries to persuade his best friend Harry Hunter to drop his mistress Carol Corman and return to his wife Mary, other romantic problems suddenly spring to life.

Title: 96. Pretty Poison
description: When a mentally-disturbed young man tells a pretty girl that he's a secret agent, she believes him; murder and mayhem ensue.

Title: 97. The Astro-Zombies
description: The Plan - to build a super human. How? By murdering innocent, convenient victims, and using various bits of them. The result? Creatures on the rampage.

Title: 98. Wild in the Streets
description: A young man gains significant political influence as the leader of a counterculture rock band with his rallying cry of voting rights for teenagers.

Title: 99. Naked You Die
description: After a mysterious trunk arrives at a prestigious girl's boarding school, its staff and students - including an orphaned heiress and an amateur sleuth - are targeted by a shadowy murderer.

Title: 100. The Wicked Die Slow
description: "The Kid," a notorious gunfighter, and his Mexican sidekick Armadillo ride through the post-Civil War West looking for four Indians who raped the Kid's girl friend.

Title: 101. Bandolero!
description: Mace Bishop (James Stewart) masquerades as a hangman in order to save his outlaw brother, Dee (Dean Martin), from the gallows, runs to Mexico chased by Sheriff July Johnson's (George Kennedy's) posse and fights against Mexican bandits.

Title: 102. No Way to Treat a Lady
description: A crafty serial killer plays a game of cat-and-mouse with a harried police detective trying to track him down.

Title: 103. The Crimson Cult
description: Robert Manning visits the remote country house where his brother Peter was last seen. While his host seems outwardly friendly and his niece more demonstrably so, Robert detects a feeling of menace in the air.

Title: 104. A Dandy in Aspic
description: The British and Soviet intelligence services attempt to out-fox one another using the homesick double-agent Krasnevin, a.k.a. Alexander Eberlin, as a pawn in a complex spy-game that takes place in Berlin.

Title: 105. Inspector Clouseau
description: A string of robberies has occurred in Britain and it's up to Inspector Clouseau to catch the criminal.

Title: 106. The Ruthless Four
description: Four men embark on a mission to unearth a fortune in gold from a mine.

Title: 107. The Killing of Sister George
description: The life of a soap opera actress begins to unravel as she fears her character will be written out of the series.

Title: 108. Woman in Chains
description: An art gallery owner's photography hobby reveals a dark side, catching the attention of an artist's wife who's drawn to him despite her stable marriage.

Title: 109. The Detective
description: While grappling with his wife's infidelity, an NYPD detective investigates the murder of a gay man, which he discovers is linked to official corruption involving sex and drugs.

Title: 110. Anzio
description: A war correspondent witnesses errors of the Allied Command after he and a unit of US Army Rangers land unopposed at Anzio, Italy, but later become trapped behind German lines during one of the bloodiest battles of WWII.

Title: 111. Dark of the Sun
description: A band of mercenaries led by Captain Curry travel through war-torn Congo across deadly terrain, battling rival armies, to steal $50 million in uncut diamonds. But infighting, sadistic rebels and a time lock jeopardize everything.

Title: 112. Corruption
description: A doctor goes to extreme lengths--even murder--to restore the badly burned face of his fiancée.

Title: 113. Shalako
description: A group of European aristocrats go hunting in New Mexico in the 1880s. Here they quickly come into conflict with the Apaches, who are reluctant to see guests on their reservation. Only the recluse Shalako seems able to save them.

Title: 114. Deep Inside
description: A manipulative woman delights in exploiting her friends' weaknesses during a beachside summer until her machinations lead to murder and her friends finally see through her.

Title: 115. Death Laid an Egg
description: The depraved manager of a high-tech poultry factory is pulled into a love triangle with his domineering wife and her sexually-liberated cousin, leading to double-crosses and murder.

Title: 116. Madigan
description: In New York City's Spanish Harlem, detectives Madigan and Bonaro are given 72 hours by their superior to capture a hoodlum wanted for homicide in Brooklyn.

Title: 117. The Night They Raided Minsky's
description: A naive young Amish woman runs away from her home in Pennsylvania to New York City, where she hopes to act in religious stage plays but ends up performing in Burlesque theatre.

Title: 118. The Rape of the Vampire
description: After a psychoanalyst unsuccessfully tries to convince four sisters that they are not 200-year-old vampires, the Queen of the Vampires promulgates the cause of the Undead.

Title: 119. Secret Ceremony
description: A penniless woman meets a strange girl who insists she is her long-lost mother, and becomes enmeshed in a web of deception, and perhaps madness.

Title: 120. Wonderwall
description: Professor Oscar Collins becomes obsessed with model Penny Lane and her boyfriend, drilling holes in their chaotic apartment and engaging in daydreams and delusions.

Title: 121. Mayerling
description: Based on real life events that led to tragic deaths of Crown Prince Rudolf of Austria and his lover Baroness Mary Vetsera.

Title: 122. 2 - I, a Woman, Part II
description: Newly married to a sexually perverted antique dealer, Siv submits herself to endless degradation before discovering that her husband harbors a diabolical secret.

Title: 123. Up the Junction
description: Addresses some of the major 60s social issues - a bored rich London-girl from Chelsea decides to go "slumming" in depressed Battersea, getting a flat and starts factory-work and makes friends... of which one has to get an illegal abortion.

Title: 124. The Olsen Gang
description: Egon Olsen's criminal trio always gets into unlucky, comical situations when executing Egon's genius plans. After release from prison, he already has a new plan: steal a valuable German item from a secured museum in Copenhagen.

Title: 125. Asterix and Cleopatra
description: Cleopatra decides to prove to Julius Caesar that her people are not decadent by building a palace in less than three months. When Cleopatra's architect asks the Gallic druid Getafix for help, Asterix and Obelix accompany him to Egypt.

Title: 126. 5 Card Stud
description: The players in an ongoing poker game are being mysteriously killed off, one by one.

Title: 127. The Girls
description: Three Swedish stage actresses give differing interpretations of the classic Aristophanes play "Lysistrata."

Title: 128. Deadfall
description: Cat burglar Henry Clarke and his accomplices Richard and Fe Moreau attempt to steal diamonds from the chateau of millionaire Salinas. However, Henry's partners in crime aren't the most emotionally stable people.

Title: 129. The Ghastly Ones
description: Three married couples are forced to spend the night in a Victorian-era house where they start getting killed off by a deranged psycho who's bent on claiming an inheritance they are all entitled to.

Title: 130. Succubus
description: A performer at an S&M nightclub begins to lose her grip on reality, and is plunged into a nightmarish mental landscape.

Title: 131. Voyage to the Planet of Prehistoric Women
description: Astronauts landing on Venus encounter dangerous creatures and almost meet some sexy Venusian women who like to sun-bathe in hip-hugging skin-tight pants and seashell brassieres.

Title: 132. Mafia
description: The new chief of the Carabinieri in a small Sicilian town must fight corrupt officials, the frightened silence of witnesses and the local Mafia boss to solve a murder.

Title: 133. The Sweet Ride
description: At a Malibu rented house, a tennis hustler, a surfer and a musician enjoy a Bohemian lifestyle, fall in-love with an unexpected female visitor and fight off a motorcycle punk gang.

Title: 134. Django, Prepare a Coffin
description: A gunfighter forms a gang of "deceased" execution victims to get revenge on the politician and outlaw who killed his wife.

Title: 135. Fando and Lis
description: Fando and his partially-paralyzed lover Lis search for the mythical city of Tar. Based on Jodorowsky's memories of a play by surrealist Fernando Arrabal.

Title: 136. Capricious Summer
description: The friends enjoy the charms of nature - and of their guests.

Title: 137. The Fixer
description: In Czarist Russia, around 1911, a Russian-Jewish handyman, Yakov Bok (Sir Alan Bates), is wrongly imprisoned for a most unlikely crime.

Title: 138. Here We Go Round the Mulberry Bush
description: A high-school dropout, obsessed with sex, is determined to lose his virginity.

Title: 139. The Green Slime
description: After destroying a giant asteroid heading towards Earth, a group of scientists unknowingly bring back a strange green substance that soon mutates into a monster.

Title: 140. The Biggest Bundle of Them All
description: Harry Price, Juliana and some incompetent European gangsters kidnap an American gangster who they think has a lot of money.

Title: 141. How to Make a Doll
description: A nerdy professor who has no luck with women builds beautiful female robots to satisfy his sexual desires.

Title: 142. Toby Dammit
description: During a trip to Rome, a debauched Shakespearian actor is tormented by the Italian film industry, fans, the press and the Devil, who appears as a little girl seeking to collect his head.

Title: 143. The Libertine
description: After discovering her late husband's swinger's pad, a widow uses the apartment to explore her own sexuality, while searching for a man who can reciprocate her passions.

Title: 144. Petulia
description: An unhappily married socialite finds solace in the company of a recently divorced doctor.

Title: 145. Signs of Life
description: Three wounded soldiers are removed from battle and given the task of looking after a fortress in a small coastal town. However, the pressures of isolation begin to take their toll on the men.

Title: 146. Mandabi
description: A money order from a relative in Paris throws the life of a Senegalese family man out of order. He deals with corruption, greed, problematic family members, the locals and the changing from his traditional way of living to a more modern one.

Title: 147. If You Meet Sartana Pray for Your Death
description: A gadget-laden gunfighter and gambler interferes with the complex schemes of gangsters and dignitaries hoping to steal a bank's gold and obtain the insurance payout for its theft.

Title: 148. The Shakiest Gun in the West
description: A pardoned stagecoach robber, becomes government agent and marries a naive unsuspecting east-coast dentist in order to join a wagon train and catch the smugglers who have been selling guns to the Indians.

Title: 149. Sebastian
description: During the Cold War, the chief of a British intelligence code-breaking section falls in love with a new employee and shields an old co-worker accused of Communist affiliations from the wrath of the security branch.

Title: 150. Star!
description: A musical biography of Gertrude Lawrence, who led a hustling and bustling life on the stage.

Title: 151. Hot Millions
description: Paroled London fraudster Marcus Pendleton poses as a computer specialist in order to work for an insurance company that entirely relies on its corporate server.

Title: 152. Ace High
description: A Greek bandit forms an unlikely alliance with two bounty hunters and an acrobat to take his revenge on the people who framed him.

Title: 153. Guns for San Sebastian
description: In 1743, outlaw Leon Alastray is hunted by the Spanish army but is given sanctuary by a priest in a village terrorized by marauding Yaqui Indians.

Title: 154. Ho!
description: The quest for respect of a small time mob driver turns him into a notorious gangster.

Title: 155. Three in the Attic
description: When three coeds discover that the campus Casanova is dating them all at once, they lock him up in an attic and take turns having sex with him... to drain the stud of his potency.

Title: 156. The Blood Beast Terror
description: A scientist genetically engineers a creature that transforms between a Death's-head moth and a woman. The creature poses as the scientist's daughter to lure victims when in human form, then feeds on their blood as a moth.

Title: 157. Joanna
description: A provincial girl is entangled in the mod morality of London.

Title: 158. She Mob
description: A gang of four lesbian inmates escapes from prison and kidnaps the boyfriend of a wealthy woman. She hires a tough private eye to find her boyfriend and rescue him.

Title: 159. Uptight
description: In this landmark collaboration between activist and actress Ruby Dee and director Jules Dassin, Black revolutionaries are betrayed by one of their own. Based on the 1935 classic "The Informer."

Title: 160. The Power
description: One by one members of a special project team are being killed by telekinesis - the ability to move things with the power of the mind alone. The race is to determine which of the remaining team members is the murderer and how to stop them.

Title: 161. My Prostitute Love
description: Halil is an honest greengrocer with an ordinary life. One day his friends take him to a local night club where he meets a beautiful hostess, Sabiha. The two fall in love. Little does Sabiha know about Halil's life before they met.

Title: 162. Bora Bora
description: A Frenchman finds his runaway wife on an island in the Pacific.

Title: 163. Les Biches
description: Architect Paul Thomas insinuates himself into the relationship of two bisexual women living in a St. Tropez villa with tragic consequences.

Title: 164. Birds in Peru
description: On a beach, a group of sailors have sex with a depressed young woman. Madam of a nearby brothel takes her in but she leaves with an artist who lives close by. Meanwhile, her old rich husband and his sinister chauffeur are looking for her.

Title: 165. Die Nichten der Frau Oberst
description: Young widow Madame Yanne takes care of her pretty nieces Florentine and Juliet, who are currently living out their lesbian obsessions and are currently more engaged with each other than turning their heads around the lusty male world.

Title: 166. The Sweet Body of Deborah
description: A sexy newlywed couple visits the husband's hometown in Geneva, where they are subjected to threats stemming from the death of his former fiancée.

Title: 167. Stars of Eger
description: 1552, the great Turkish Empire wants to conquer Europe, and the world. The last stand is Hungarian Kingdom, and the castle of Eger. The brave soldiers decides they will fight till the end of their lives.

Title: 168. Monterey Pop
description: A film about the greatest pre-Woodstock rock music festival.

Title: 169. The Brotherhood
description: The son of a powerful Mafia don comes home from his army service in Vietnam and wants to lead his own life, but family tradition, intrigues and powerplays involving his older brother dictate otherwise, and he finds himself being slowly drawn back into that world.

Title: 170. Valentín de la Sierra
description: This film was based on the Mexican folk song "Corrido Valentin de la Sierra" which recounts the exploits of the famous revolutionary who led an uprising during the revolution.

Title: 171. The Snow Woman
description: The lives of a master sculptor and his young apprentice are changed forever when they meet an evil witch during a snow storm.

Title: 172. Without a Stitch
description: When a high-school girl complains of her inability to reach sexual climax, her doctor suggests that she keep a diary of her sexual encounters. She does just that and soon finds herself caught up in a sexual merry-go-round that includes making a hardcore porno film in Sweden, an escapade with a German sadist and a lesbian encounter.

Title: 173. Padosan
description: A simple man from a village falls in love with his new neighbor. He enlists the help of his musical-theater friends to woo the lovely girl-next-door away from her music teacher.

Title: 174. Raja Aur Runk
description: Mark Twain's story "The Prince and the Pauper" is transplanted to an Indian setting with all of the essential elements intact.

Title: 175. Die Lümmel von der ersten Bank - 1. Trimester: Zur Hölle mit den Paukern
description: Collectable stamps trader Kurt Nietnagel's son Pepe recently transferred from a private boarding school to Mommsen gymnasium (classical high school), but is also already its king of pranksters. Latin teacher Dr. Knörz swears to get rid of Pepe, but a staged suicide means his own exit. Dr. Knörz's replacement, Dr. Kersten, proves a teacher to the rascals' liking. However headmaster Dr. Gottlieb Taft dislikes him for dating his daughter Helena. Now the boys actually come to a teacher's rescue, again trough daring pranks.

Title: 176. The Fiction-Makers
description: The Saint's asked to act as a bodyguard to the best-selling adventure author Amos Klein, a young woman who uses a male pen-name.

Title: 177. The Horse in the Gray Flannel Suit
description: Frederick Bolton has to solve two problems. First, his boss has instructed him to come up with a reasonable campaign to promote a new product, a stomach pill named "Aspercel" - by tomorrow. The second problem is Fred's daughter, Helen. She is absolutely fond of horses, takes riding classes and has already had decent success in some competitions. Her biggest wish is to own a horse herself, a dream her father cannot afford at all. Now Fred tries to solve both problems at once by simply combining them: A horse named "Aspercel", ridden by his daughter should bring the name of the pill into the papers and make Helen happy, too. But there's still one more obstacle: Helen and Aspercel of course have to win a few jumping competitions to make this idea work.

Title: 178. Assignment K
description: A British Agent, posing as an executive of a toy company, tangles with East European spies in various European locales.

Title: 179. Sexy Susan Sins Again
description: A count tasks seductive Susan and her friends to stop an assassination plot against Napoleon in this historical sex comedy that's part of "Frau Wirtin..." movie franchise.

Title: 180. Run, Man, Run
description: A knife-wielding Mexican ne'er-do-well is tasked by a scholar with locating $3 million in revolutionary gold, and finds himself working and competing with various parties for it.

Title: 181. Come Play with Me
description: Young Alvise's body is paralyzed, or at least he thinks so. He is infatuated by his beautiful aunt Lea. What starts as innocent therapy and care soon develops into strange erotic and psychological battle between them.

Title: 182. The Seduction of Inga
description: The Seduction of Inga is Joseph Sarno's sizzling and controversial sequel to his 1967 erotic masterpiece, Inga, starring the young, voluptuous Swedish sensation Marie Liljedahl in her steamiest role ever.

Title: 183. The Last Roman
description: Cethegus, leader of the Roman nobility, travels to Bizantium and its leader Justinian, in an attempt to raise an army to march on the Goths under Narses. Cethegus would like to set the two sides to war against each other, that his own forces might take control at the outcome.

Title: 184. Death by Hanging
description: A Korean man is sentenced to death by hanging, but he survives the execution. For the following two hours, his executioners try to work out how to handle the situation in this black farce.

Title: 185. Kong Island
description: Eve is a jungle girl brought up by apes. She is captured with a number of apes by a mad scientist, conducting mind control experiments on them. Eventually she is liberated by a young explorer.

Title: 186. The Belle Star Story
description: After abuse by men, Belle Starr becomes their equal in riding, shooting, and gambling, often in men's clothes. Her rocky romance with Larry Blackie leads to a failed robbery. She saves him, but they part ways, hoping to meet again.

Title: 187. A Sky Full of Stars for a Roof
description: Two drifters meet and soon become travelling companions. But one of them, Tim (Gemma), is being chased by a crazed killer and his band of gunmen to settle an old score. The two (Adore being the other) are chased through the west, encountering scrape after scrape until the killers catch up and the score is settled for good.

Title: 188. Love After Death
description: During a cataleptic fit, Montel is buried alive--a burial plotted by his greedy wife Sofia with several men, including her lover, Montel's doctor. Exiting his grave, Montel goes on a sexual rampage. When the conspirators engage in gunplay at an abandoned castle, Montel arrives to stab the doctor and strangle Sofia, followed by the revelation that he is actually dead.

Title: 189. The Secret War of Harry Frigg
description: In 1943, a group of captured Allied brigadier generals cannot agree on an escape plan. Allied headquarters develops a plan to send in an escape artist to be captured himself so he can coordinate the generals escape.

Title: 190. Murder à la Mod
description: Naive young Karen wants to help her struggling amateur-filmmaker boyfriend Christopher raise enough money so he can divorce his wife. Meanwhile, jolly psycho prankster Otto stalks the building where Christopher is shooting a low-grade adult movie in order to keep himself afloat.

Title: 191. How I Became a Nudist
description: A young model and her friends vacation at a horse ranch. The owner of the ranch is a nudist and takes the girls to a nudist camp to show them the wonders of nudism.

Title: 192. The Birthday Party
description: The down-at-heel lodger in a seaside boarding house is menaced by two mysterious strangers, who eventually take him away.

Title: 193. Project X
description: A spy is brought back from cryogenic suspension after being almost killed in a plane crash returning from a mission to learn about a deadly new weapon being developed in the East. But the vital memories are being suppressed, so the authorities use ultra-advanced technologies to try to uncover the secret.

Title: 194. Duffy
description: Duffy is a cunning aristocrat of criminals hired by young playboy Stefane to hijack a boat carrying several million dollars of his father's riches. He succeeds, with help from Stefane's girlfriend, but there's an unexpected turn of events.

Title: 195. The Subject Was Roses
description: A young man returning home from World War II finds himself caught up in his parents' turbulent relationship.

Title: 196. Girl in Gold Boots
description: A young woman leaves her job as a waitress and travels to Los Angeles, where she strives to become the top star in the glamorous world of go-go dancing.

Title: 197. Very Happy Alexander
description: Alexandre, a young and honest farmer under the yoke of an authoritarian wife, works around the clock in the fields. When she dies in a car accident, it's a holiday for Alexandre.

Title: 198. The Gendarme Gets Married
description: The gendarme Cruchot meets the widow Josepha. They quickly fall in love but Cruchot's daughter doesn't like Josepha and is determined to prevent the wedding by all means necessary.

Title: 199. Koritsia ston ilio
description: A shepherd falls in love with an English tourist in Greece.

Title: 200. Castle of the Creeping Flesh
description: In an ancient castle, a mad scientist is trying to revive his dead daughter by an operation, but there are certain body parts he needs that he can't get. His problem is solved when a group of drunken party-goers stumble into his castle.

Title: 201. Salt and Pepper
description: An African American and a Briton, who own a nightclub in Soho, London, get mixed up in an intriguing plot when an intelligence agent is murdered in the club. Soon, they find themselves the target of a dangerous organization.

Title: 202. Bye Bye Braverman
description: Four Jewish intellectuals carpool to the funeral of their old friend Leslie Braverman, who died suddenly at age 41.

Title: 203. Horus: Prince of the Sun
description: A boy with a mythical sword wants to protect a Norse village from an evil ice wizard and his minions, who destroyed his family's village. However, the villagers don't fully trust him and a mysterious girl with a dark secret befriends him.

Title: 204. Sweet November
description: A woman lures emotionally crippled men into affairs, then helps them repair their lives.

Title: 205. Psych-Out
description: A deaf runaway is taken in by a psychedelic band while searching for her missing brother in San Francisco's Haight-Ashbury hippie district.

Title: 206. Mad Doctor of Blood Island
description: A man who loves to travel, travels to an island where a mad doctor is creating zombies.

Title: 207. Gamera vs. Viras
description: Gamera the Flying Turtle falls under the spell of evil aliens, but two children free him and he returns to fight the aliens' monster, Viras.

Title: 208. No Tears for the Damned
description: A man driven insane by his adulterous wife and domineering mother terrorizes the city of Las Vegas, brutally murdering sex workers and showgirls. This very low budget film, marketed for drive-in and "grindhouse" exhibition, was presumed lost until its rediscovery and re-release by Vinegar Syndrome.

Title: 209. Beware the Black Widow
description: Investigators enlist the aid of a call girl to capture a dangerous killer preying on local mobsters.

Title: 210. Kekec's Tricks
description: Children's film about the witty boy Kekec and his friends, and their adventures in the mountains of Slovenia, during the summer.

Title: 211. La bambolona
description: A bachelor attorney with a roving eye for beautiful women sets his sights on a young student for his next amorous conquest.

Title: 212. Villa Rides
description: Mexican rebel Pancho Villa leads a revolution helped by an American aviator imprisoned in Mexico.

Title: 213. The Mini-Skirt Mob
description: Driven by jealousy, the jilted leader of a female motorcycle gang instigates a sadistic reign of terror against her ex-lover and his new bride.

Title: 214. Jet Generation
description: In the "Swinging Munich" of the late 1960s: The young millionaire daughter Carroll Buchheim, an American, flew from the United States to Germany to visit her brother, who lives here.

Title: 215. The Pick-Up
description: Two mob money couriers, Frankie and Tony, have their latest package of $1 million stolen by two con women, Dana and Marcia, in which the men must find the women to recover the money before they become marked men.

Title: 216. A Black Veil for Lisa
description: While trying to solve a series of murders, a possessive narcotics detective hires a hit-man to kill his unfaithful wife, but the hunter and the hunted soon begin an affair.

Title: 217. Nanami: The Inferno of First Love
description: A teenage goldsmith with a dark past tragically falls in love with a young nude model.

Title: 218. Where Were You When the Lights Went Out?
description: During a blackout, a New York executive crosses paths with a Broadway actress and her husband.

Title: 219. Seeds of Sin
description: An angry and alcoholic matriarch tyrannizes her spoiled, grown-up, children during an unwanted family get-together, where someone begins killing them one by one.

Title: 220. Cry Wolf
description: An Imaginative young boy called Tony whose Dad is the Town Mayor, isn't believed when he might actually be telling the truth for once.

Title: 221. I Am Curious (Blue)
description: Told in a quasi-documentary style, this companion piece to I Am Curious (Yellow) (1967) deals with topics such as class society, religion, sex, contraceptives, and the Swedish prison Kumla.

Title: 222. Two Girls for a Madman
description: Two young girls studying to be ballet dancers in New York City are chosen by a crazed sex fiend to be his next victims. He rapes one of them at gunpoint, then goes on to stalk and terrorize both of them.

Title: 223. The Hour of the Furnaces
description: Divided into three segments, namely 1 Neocolonialism, 2 Act for liberation, 3 Violence and liberation, the documentary lasts more than 4 hours this deals with the defense of the revolution and the revolution of the third world such as the revolt of the students in the United States and Western Europe, Czech citizens protest against the Soviet Union's State bureaucracy and also the revolution that (probably) is unprecedented in Argentina.

Title: 224. Jennie: Wife/Child
description: Seeds of revenge become planted in an old farmer's mind after he learns that his child bride is getting cozy with the hired help.

Title: 225. Therese and Isabelle
description: Two young girls experience awakening sexuality in the heated atmosphere of a Swiss girls' boarding school...

Title: 226. How Sweet It Is!
description: Photographer Grif, wife Jenny, and son Davey travel to Paris. Jenny inadvertently rents a French lawyer's home. Grif and Jenny face romantic temptations while navigating the awkward living situation, testing their commitment to each other.

Title: 227. Frankenstein's Bloody Terror
description: A man suffers from the curse of lycanthropy and seeks out the aid of a German doctor and his wife who are experts in the occult. Unknowingly, the cursed man has summoned two vampires instead, who have sinister plans of their own for the werewolf.

Title: 228. Brides of Blood
description: Natives of a tropical island have to contend with man-eating plants and animals, mutations caused by radioactivity. Virgin sacrifices become the norm. A small group of interlopers become caught up in the mayhem.

Title: 229. Nude Django
description: A schoolteacher arrives in town with the map to a gold mine. The lesbian dance-hall owner schemes to steal the map.

Title: 230. The Sex of Angels
description: Four people (three women and a man) set off on a boat trip through the fjords of Yugoslavia. Two of the women are lesbian lovers. Influenced by LSD, the female passengers freely engage in nudity.

Title: 231. Stay Away, Joe
description: A mixed-race American Indian rodeo champ returns to the reservation to help his people out.

Title: 232. Boom!
description: Explores the confrontation between the woman who has everything, including emptiness, and a penniless poet who has nothing but the ability to fill a wealthy woman's needs.

Title: 233. I Live for Your Death
description: Mike Sturges and his younger brother, Roy, are sentenced to Yuma Penitentiary on a trumped-up train robbery charge. Both endure cruel treatment before Mike escapes to extract revenge on their enemies.

Title: 234. A Place for Lovers
description: Julia, a fashion designer harboring a secret, spends ten days of passion in the Alps with Valerio, a race car driver, in what will be their last vacation together.

Title: 235. Finders Keepers, Lovers Weepers!
description: Paul, the owner of a topless go-go bar on the Sunset Strip, is unaware of his wife's affair with the hunky bartender and his girlfriend's plan to rob the club.

Title: 236. The Impossible Years
description: The eldest daughter of a Professor of Psychology at a large conservative university causes havoc, and great embarrassment, for her father with her free-willed and uninhibited lifestyle.

Title: 237. The Valley of the Bees
description: Set in 13th-century central Europe, a young boy joins the Teutonic Knights. Years later, he leaves the Crusaders, pursued by a fanatical comrade. He faces repercussions for rejecting the Holy Order.

Title: 238. Ankhen
description: Shortly after independence India faces terrorists attacks in Assam, resulting in many deaths and casualties. A group of concerned citizens then decide to do something to stop this carnage.

Title: 239. Today We Kill, Tomorrow We Die!
description: A man released after a jail term for a crime he did not commit, raises a gang to go after the man who framed him.

Title: 240. The Man Who Lies
description: On the run from pursuing soldiers, a man hides in a small European town.

Title: 241. Never a Dull Moment
description: Actor Jack Albany, who plays gangsters on TV, is mistaken for notorious hit-man Ace, and is hired by mob boss Leo Smooth to pull a heist, but Jack must find a way out of it.

Title: 242. High School
description: Documentary filmmaker Frederick Wiseman takes us inside Northeast High School as a fly on the wall to observe the teachers and how they interact with the students.

Title: 243. The Saucy Guy
description: A poor young man who works at a gas station devises various ways in order to find and marry a rich bride.

Title: 244. Yokai Monsters: 100 Monsters
description: The local yôkai (Japanese spirits) interfere to avenge a murder and thwart the plans of corrupt officials.

Title: 245. The Touchables
description: British rock star with a love-'em-and-leave-'em reputation. The tables are turned when four cute young girls kidnap the singer. After several days of sex and degradation, the poor fellow is rescued by his friends.

Title: 246. Her Private Hell
description: A young Italian girl comes to London and is tricked into posing nude for risqué magazines.

Title: 247. Robby
description: Shipwrecked on a tropical island, a young boy befriends an abandoned native youth, forcing him to reevaluate societal prejudice about race, religion and nudity.

Title: 248. The Boys of Paul Street
description: In Budapest, two rival gangs of young boys lay claim to a vacant lot. The hostilities escalate yet never quite boil over into actual violence. The film poignantly portrays the struggles and resilience of youth amid the harsh realities of war.

Title: 249. Gungala, the Black Panther Girl
description: An insurance company, led by a wealthy English family, organized an expedition to Africa to find a lost heiress who has been raised in the wild as Gungala and one of the explorers falls in love with her.

Title: 250. Blonde on a Bum Trip
description: A naive young college student, who is majoring in chemistry, is persuaded by her roommates and a would-be drug dealer to make LSD for them, and she winds up getting caught up in the "acid" lifestyle.

Title: 251. She-Devils on Wheels
description: An all-female motorcycle gang, called 'The Maneaters' hold motorcycle races, as well as terrorize the residents of a small Florida town, and clash off against an all-male rival gang of hot-riders.

Title: 252. Paper Lion
description: Sportswriter George Plimpton poses as a rookie quarterback for the Detroit Lions for a "Sports Illustrated" article.

Title: 253. Beyond the Law
description: A trio of thieves plot to steal a town's silver shipment but a turn of events makes them the town's heroes.

Title: 254. A Thousand Pleasures
description: Henpecked misogynist Richard Davis murders his shrewish wife and goes out to dispose of her corpse. However, things go awry for Richard after he's abducted by a pair of insane lesbians who take him to their house where they keep a grown woman called Baby in a crib.

Title: 255. The Legend of Lylah Clare
description: A dictatorial film director (Peter Finch) hires an unknown actress (Kim Novak) to play the lead role in a planned movie biography of a late, great Hollywood star.

Title: 256. House of Cards
description: In 1960s Paris, an American boxer stumbles upon an international fascist conspiracy that aims to create a new world order.

Title: 257. The Wicked Dreams of Paula Schultz
description: A beautiful East German Olympic hopeful pole-vaults over the Berlin Wall to freedom.

Title: 258. A Lovely Way to Die
description: A cop quits the force after too much disappointment in the system and becomes bodyguard to a rich recent widow on trial for her husband's murder. He decides to help her clear her name--and get over her husband.

Title: 259. Peony Lantern
description: On the night of the summer Obon festival, Hagiwara Shinzaburo meets a beautiful courtesan named Otsuyu. Not knowing she's a ghost, he becomes infatuated by her.

Title: 260. Thar She Blows!
description: A wealthy industrialist charters a yacht and hires a pimp to bring some women along.

Title: 261. Soldaterkammerater på bjørnetjeneste
description: A comedy about life among a group of Danish soldiers stationed in the country-side with a real bear and a small boy joining them.

Title: 262. Sweden: Heaven and Hell
description: It shows contraceptives for teen girls, lesbian nightclubs, wife swapping, porno movies, biker gangs, and Walpurgis Night celebrations. It also examines Sweden's purported drug, drinking and suicide problems.

Title: 263. Criminal Affair
description: A renowned author, college professor and criminologist is given a year off in order to write his latest book. His arrival in Buenos Aires gives him the opportunity to work on his true project, planning and pulling off the perfect crime.

Title: 264. Kill!
description: Two ronin - an ex-samurai and an ex-farmer - get caught up in a local official's complex game of murder and betrayal.

Title: 265. The Sea Gull
description: Film adaptation of Anton Chekhov's story of life in rural Russia during the latter part of the 19th century.

Title: 266. The Zombie Walks
description: A serial killer who calls himself "The Laughing Corpse" dresses up in a skeleton costume and kills his victims with a poison-filled scorpion-shaped ring.

Title: 267. For Love of Ivy
description: Upon learning their maid will be leaving to earn an education, the son of the family decides to set her up with a man.

Title: 268. Oedipus the King
description: This classic (Greek) tale tells how a noble youth accidentally marries his own mother, kills his own father (deliberately) and ends up paying a terrible price for invoking the wrath of the Gods.

Title: 269. Sappho '68
description: Small-town girl Jennifer Bradley moves to San Francisco to carve out a successful career as a photographer, but she soon gets caught up in the sexual revolution that's going on around her. After too many unsatisfying relationships with men, she becomes involved with lesbian model Belinda Frazier.

Title: 270. Goke, Body Snatcher from Hell
description: The survivors of a plane crash in a remote area are attacked by blob-like alien creatures that turn their victims into blood-thirsty vampires.

Title: 271. Snow Treasure
description: This movie is based on a book by Marie McSwigan. It is 1940 in Norway, a neutral, peace-loving country that is invaded by Nazi Germany. A gang of Norwegian children do what Norwegian children like to do best - ski.

Title: 272. Symbiopsychotaxiplasm: Take One
description: Filmmaker William Greaves auditioned acting students for a fictional drama, while simultaneously shooting the behind-the-scenes drama taking place.

Title: 273. The Anniversary
description: Three sons who work in the family construction business help their overbearing mother celebrate her anniversary to her late husband.

Title: 274. Commandos
description: During World War II, an Italian-American commando outfit disguised as an Italian Army unit is parachuted behind Axis lines in North Africa.

Title: 275. Hauptmann Florian von der Mühle
description: This story of the miller Florian, who gave all his money to the war against Napoleon, is loosely based on a true story. After the war, Florian's reimbursement is challenged, and he must also pay taxes on his destroyed mill. He resists the tax collectors and takes off to Vienna, where he intends to defend his rights. On the way, he rescues the Duchess of Guastalla from assault. She also wants to go to Vienna, as His Majesty Franz II is trying to contest an heir in her favor. With cunning, luck, and dagger, Florian fights his way through a slew of nobility and their secret police. In the end, he acquires multiple titles, and the Duchess acquires him.

Title: 276. Charlie Bubbles
description: A married writer has an affair with his secretary.

Title: 277. Black Lizard
description: Japanese sixties comedy featuring a cunning female jewel thief named Black Lizard who tries to kidnap Sanaye, a wealthy jeweler's beautiful daughter as part of a plot to steal the jeweler's expensive "Star of Egypt" diamond. To thwart the planned kidnapping, the jeweler hires Japan's number one detective, the brilliant Akechi. This sets off a dual between Black Lizard and Akechi as each tries to outwit the other. In the process, the two adversaries develop a mutual respect and affection for each other. Despite Akechi's efforts, Black Lizard and her crew are able to kidnap Sanaye and gain possession of the "Star of Egypt". Black Lizard takes Sanaye to her secret lair on a remote island which is populated by an eerie collection of naked human dolls. There Black Lizard plans to preserve Sanaye's beauty forever by turning her into one of her dolls. As Sanaye's doom quickly approaches, it is up to Akechi to save the day.

Title: 278. Lucia
description: Traces episodes in the lives of three Cuban women, each named Lucía, from three different historical periods: the Cuban war of independence (with Spain), the 1930s, and the 1960s.

Title: 279. Prudence and the Pill
description: Wealthy London banker Gerald Hardcastle, his wife Prudence, his mistress, and his family and servants all get involved in comic hi-jinks when they swap birth-control medicines in an effort to deceive each other.

Title: 280. Office Love-in
description: A secretary at a computer dating service unknowingly dates her own boss, his wife, and his two sons.

Title: 281. Coplan sauve sa peau
description: In Istanbul, a young woman is attacked by six thugs and the agent Frank Milland who had set a rendez-vous with her, is outnumbered, and she dies. Frank is menaced later in order to stop his inquiry about the thugs identities. Each clue he follows leads to more and more danger. Then he comes across Eva, a young woman who is the dead girl's spitting image; either she is her twin sister, or the woman who died in his arms. Eventually he encounters a mad sculptor, who is more than he pretends to be. Frank ends up a prisoner is an abandoned castle hidden in Turkey's mountainous hinterland, trying to save his own life and to prevent the development of a mysterious weapon that would put an end to civilization as we know it.

Title: 282. What's So Bad About Feeling Good?
description: A new infection that simply makes people feel happy is treated as a threat by the authorities while its "victims" work to spread it to others.

Title: 283. Satanik
description: A withered old hag turns into a beautiful young woman after drinking a youth formula.

Title: 284. El grito
description: A documentary on the student movement in Mexico, 1968, made by film students

Title: 286. Young Wolves
description: Alain, "a young wolf", elegant and racy, is maintained by the princess Linzani. At the same time, he goes out with a girl of his age, Sylvie, who despite her bold attitude has never had a lover.

Title: 287. Partner
description: Bernardo Bertolucci, along with co-scenarist Gianni Amico, used Dostoievski's 1846, pre-imprisonment novella The Double: A Petersburg Poem, which they moved to Italy and updated to the pro-Vietcong student-protest present.

Title: 288. Profound Desires of the Gods
description: An engineer from Tokyo arrives on a drought-ridden tropical island to drill a well to power a nearby sugar mill. He meets the inbred Futori family, hated by the locals for breaking religious customs.

Title: 289. Speedway
description: Poor bookkeeping saddles stock-car driver Steve Grayson with a huge bill for back taxes which hampers his ability to continue racing competitively.

Title: 290. Just for the Hell of It
description: A young teenage boy is blamed for a Florida neighborhood being terrorized. But the real culprits are a gang of four punks leading a group of local delinquents on a nihilistic lifestyle of destruction and mayhem.

Title: 291. The Vengeance of She
description: Carol, a beautiful young girl is possessed by Ayesha's spirit who was once the queen of Kuma. Ayesha's spirit gains control over Carol to achieve her malevolent goals.

Title: 292. The Strange Affair
description: When rookie P.C. Strange falls for an under aged girl, he is unknowingly compromised by a pair of pornographers. Meanwhile, seasoned Det. Pierce is out to catch mob boss Quince and soon both plots intertwine.

Title: 293. They Call Us Misfits
description: The first entry in a series of films about the lives of social misfits Kenneth 'Kenta' Gustafsson and Gustav 'Stoffe' Svensson.

Title: 294. Flesh
description: A man desperate for money and no income, turns prostitute and interplays with a variety of clients and hustlers.

Title: 295. Indecent Desires
description: Zeb finds a doll and a ring in a garbage can. Then, he sees Ann going to work with her friend Babs. He thinks she looks like the doll. When he gets home, he caresses the doll... Ann feels it! When Zeb finds out about Ann's fiance Tom, he really gets mad, burns the doll, and beats it up, which makes Ann think she's losing her mind.

Title: 296. Kill Them All and Come Back Alone
description: A mercenary and his five-man team of oddball cutthroats are tasked by a treacherous Confederate spy with infiltrating a Union Army fortress and stealing $1 million in gold.

Title: 297. The Bamboo Saucer
description: A flying saucer hidden in a Red Chinese peasant village is sought by teams from the United States and U.S.S.R. On finding it, they band together to explore the saucer and take a trip into space.

Title: 298. The Curse of Her Flesh
description: A weapons dealer who murdered his unfaithful stripper wife goes on a killing spree, bumping off exotic dancers and hookers while plotting revenge on his wife's lover.

Title: 299. Mission Mars
description: Three American astronauts who land on Mars discover the body of a frozen Russian cosmonaut and a mysterious talking orb.

Title: 300. The Tattoo
description: An art dealer wants to buy a Modigliani, which is tattooed on the back of an old soldier.

Title: 301. Hammerhead
description: An American agent has tracked down the stronghold of an evil criminal mastermind, determined to take over the world.

Title: 302. Lonesome Cowboys
description: Five lonesome cowboys get all hot & bothered at home en the range after confronting Ramona Alvarez and her nurse.

Title: 303. Find a Place to Die
description: An outcast Confederate soldier redeems himself by defending a woman against bandits willing to kill for her goldmine claim.

Title: 304. Decline and Fall... of a Birdwatcher
description: A naive young man, sent down from university, blunders through a series of bizarre adventures in which his participation is always innocent, although others don't think so.

Title: 305. The Girl with a Pistol
description: A Sicilian woman "dishonored" by her lover goes to England with a pistol intending to murder him.

Title: 306. Sergeant Ryker
description: During the Korean War Sergeant Paul Ryker is accused of defecting to Communist China and then returning to his unit as a spy. He's court-martialed and sentenced to death but his attorney believes Ryker's innocent and asks for a new trial.

Title: 307. Gatling Gun
description: Richard Gatling wants to offer the machine gun he has invented to the government, but Tarpas has other ideas and kidnaps the man along with his prototype. Tanner then tries to track them down.

Title: 308. The Kiss of Her Flesh
description: A weapons expert who murdered his unfaithful stripper wife and her lover goes on a killing spree, bumping off exotic dancers and hookers, while plotting the demise of his wife's swinging bisexual sister and her kinky boyfriend.

Title: 309. Tender Moment
description: Teenage student Olivier (Verley) meets 25 year-old Frédérique (Delon), wife of race car driver Enrico (Hossein), and start an affair. But guilt and doubt storm over Olivier's mind.

Title: 310. One + One
description: While The Rolling Stones rehearse "Sympathy for the Devil" in the studio, Godard reflects on 1968 society, politics and culture through five different vignettes.

Title: 311. Who Saw Him Die?
description: A weak and tormented teacher is pushed to the limit by his obnoxious students.

Title: 312. Vechir na Ivana Kupala
description: Piotr is a humble farm laborer living in a poor village. He wants to marry the beautiful Pidorka, but her father doesn't want to. Fortunately, the mischievous demon Bassaruv, who is at large in the country, offers him a deal.

Title: 313. The Blood of Fu Manchu
description: Fu Manchu poisons and hypnotizes ten women to bring down his enemies, including Nayland Smith, with kisses of death.

Title: 314. The Hell with Heroes
description: In 1946 North Africa, two former US Air Force pilots are forced to work for an international smuggler to get money needed for their return to civilian life after fighting in World War II.

Title: 315. The Young Animals
description: A Mexican-American student organization pushing for dismissal of a bigoted coach finds itself at war with the wealthy white students.

Title: 316. Blue
description: A young American who was raised by Mexican bandits, now must choose sides when his Mexican gang carries out violent murderous raids into U.S. border towns.

Title: 317. Lucrezia
description: Fabrizio finds refuge from thugs in a convent, and passion in the arms of Lucrezia Borgia.

Title: 318. Le petit baigneur
description: Louis-Philippe Fourchaume, another typical lead-role for French comedy superstar Louis de Funès, is the dictatorial CEO of a French company which designs and produces sail yachts, and fires in yet another tantrum his designer André Castagnier, not realizing that man is his only chance to land a vital contract with the Italian magnate Marcello Cacciaperotti. So he has to find him at his extremely rural birthplace in 'la France profonde', which proves a torturous odyssey for the spoiled rich man; when he does get there his torment is far from over: the country bumpkin refuses to resume his slavish position now the shoe is on the other foot, so Fourchaume is dragged along in the boorish family life, and at times unable to control his temper, which may cost him more credit then he painstakingly builds up...

description: Luke Barret loses his memory after a bullet grazed his head in a shoot-out in the wild West. Trying to discover the man who tried to kill him, he will discover he is a paid gunman too, and terrible truths about his family.

Title: 320. Zywot Mateusza
description: Mateusz is a weird man living a peaceful life in a remote country house by the lake. When a stranger is attracted to his beloved sister, his life starts falling apart.

Title: 321. Cauldron of Blood
description: A blind sculptor works on his magnum opus, unaware that the skeletons that he has been using for armatures are the remains of the victims of his evil wife and that he is her next target.

Title: 322. Manon 70
description: The immortal story of beautiful Manon, who - although she loves the tolerant De Grieux - takes many lovers to satisfy her thirst for luxury.

Title: 323. The Hooked Generation
description: A gang of dope peddlers sails out to meet a Cuban boat. The trouble starts when they are forced to throw their narcotics overboard and are seen by a young couple.

Title: 324. The Savage Seven
description: Mad bikers storm through an Indian reservation just to have a good ol' time.

Title: 325. The Private Navy of Sgt. O'Farrell
description: During WW2, Sgt. O'Farrell's Pacific unit is demoralized when a Japanese submarine torpedoes an American supply ship containing beer.

Title: 326. Garter Colt
description: A beautiful young woman, skilled poker player and quick on the trigger, finds love with a French spy, and puts an end to the career of Red the bandit.

Title: 327. Attack on the Iron Coast
description: During World War II, a commando leader named Major Jamie Wilson leads a group of soldiers on a suicide mission to destroy a Nazi naval stronghold on the French coast.

Title: 328. The Violent Four
description: A detective is assigned to head a manhunt for four violent bank robbers.

Title: 329. Lila
description: A topless dancer attracts, seduces, then murders the men she sleeps with. She does it with a twist, however; she kills them with garden tools.

Title: 330. The Pink Jungle
description: A South American fashion photo shoot turns into a diamond mine seeking adventure for an American photographer and his model.

Title: 331. Behind Locked Doors
description: Terry and Ann, two "swingers", spend the night in a spooky old house where they're subjected to bizarre sexual experiments by Mr. Bradley and his deranged sister.

Title: 332. One Swedish Summer
description: A young, shy and inexperienced man travels back to Sweden, to spend the summer at his mother's house. He meets a number of women with whom he has sexual relations.

Title: 333. Eve
description: Adventurer and treasure hunter Mike Yates is hoping to find a cache of Incan treasure lost in the Amazon jungle. While looking for his missing partner, he stumbles across a beautiful jungle girl named Eve. Later, he comes across Eve's grandfather, who is being swindled by a man and a young woman who is pretending to be his granddaughter Eve. Will Yates be able to expose the swindle, beat the swindlers to the lost treasure (with help from the real Eve), and reunite Eve with her grandfather before the final credits roll?

Title: 334. Mere Hamdam Mere Dost
description: Sunil lives with his mom and sister in a middle-class dwelling in Delhi, India. He works for Chopra and Co., Chartered Accountants. He comes across a beautiful woman posing for a painting, thinks she is poor and needy, and gives her a tip. The woman's name is Anita, and both are attracted to each other. Sunil and Anita intend to marry, and Sunil even introduces Anita to his mom. One day when attending a party, Sunil is shocked to learn that Anita is a multi-millionaire. Stunned at this deception, he swears he will have nothing to do with her. When Anita attempts to smooth things over, Sunil does cool down. It is then he finds out that Anita's dad, who is serving time, had killed his father, and that Anita's mother is still alive, after making her living as a prostitute.

Title: 335. Zieh dich aus, Puppe
description: Eighteen-year-old girl leaves her disapproving family to be with her boyfriend. He dumps her when her father disinherits her, but she's too proud to admit she was wrong and return home, so she ends up working at a seedy strip club.

Title: 336. The Sergeant
description: A story of a brilliant master sergeant with a great career behind him and transferred to yet another post, his attraction to a younger man eventually overrides him, to a point where his latent homosexuality, finally emerges.

Title: 337. Fanny Hill
description: The classic tale of a young woman's erotic awakening is transplanted to swinging '60s Stockholm...

Title: 338. Angelique and the Sultan
description: In the fifth and final of the Angélique series, the beautiful heroine is sold into a sultan's harem.

Title: 339. Thunderbird 6
description: Several members of the International Rescue team attend the maiden flight of Brains' revolutionary airship Skyship One, unaware that they have been lured into a deadly trap.

Title: 340. Heartbeat
description: Lucile, 25, is the beautiful mistress of Charles, a rich, good-hearted businessman. Being a kept woman suits her as she refuses to work. She is grateful to Charles for that but she does not feel true love for him. When she meets Antoine, a charming young man of her age, it is love at first sight. Living with Antoine is not as easy as it was with Charles: Lucile is forced to find a job, which she hates, and she gets pregnant and has to ask Charles for help. After having an abortion, her love for Antoine gradually fades. That is the reason why she comes back to Charles who, full of indulgence, has patiently waited for her.

Title: 341. The Magic Bird
description: In a valley, two groups of little ants - the organized and efficient Red ones and the lazy and defenseless Yellow ones - go into a war.

Title: 342. If He Hollers, Let Him Go!
description: An escaped convict goes to a small town to clear his name; to pull off his plan, he becomes part of a murder plot.

Title: 343. Creature of Destruction

description: Bespectacled pistolero Stan Ross comes to Canyon City and becomes involved with two feuding factions, after a clerk has been killed by the banker Jefferson during a botched holdup, while robbing his own bank.

Title: 345. The Strange World of Coffin Joe
description: Three episodes: A dollmaker whose dolls are eerily human, a tale of necrophilia, and a doctor proves love is dead.

Title: 346. The Insanely Sad Princess
description: A princess in love pretends to be insanely sad to get to marry the man who will make her laugh again. Only, she doesn't know her chosen one is the prince she was ordered to marry anyway...

Title: 347. Golden Swallow
description: A master swordsman leaves behind a female colleague's signature, a Golden Swallow, when killing villains, in order to lure her to his side, as he's madly in love with her, but his ego won't allow him to express it properly.

Title: 348. Don't Just Stand There
description: A young writer is sent to Europe on an assigment to finish the final chapters of a sex novel by a famous authoress who has decided to stop writing.

Title: 349. Interlude
description: A famous conductor gives an interview to a rather young journalist.

Title: 350. The Bofors Gun
description: A national service non-commissioned officer (David Warner) comes face to face with an embittered Irish Gunner (Nicol Williamson) who is determined to humiliate him.

Title: 351. The Snake Girl and the Silver-Haired Witch
description: After years at a Catholic orphanage, a young girl's life takes an unexpected turn when her long-absent father suddenly appears to reclaim her.

Title: 352. Angels from Hell
description: A destructive ex-motorcycle gang leader comes home from Vietnam to resume his life. His desire to form a powerful gang has the police running scared. But, will he succeed.

Title: 353. Genocide
description: All the insects on Earth become wild and attack humans, causing Armageddon.

Title: 354. Subterfuge
description: A C.I.A. man goes to London to assist British Intelligence uncover a mole and destroy a foreign spy ring.

description: Mr. Freedom is an all-American superhero that destroys everyone who even remotely disagrees with imperialism. The film accounts his latest assignment to save France from being taken over by the commies.

Title: 356. Requiem for a Gringo
description: A gang of desperadoes, on the run after a robbery, kills the brother of a rancher. The latter swears revenge. He hunts down the bandits and takes them out one by one.

Title: 357. Gates to Paradise
description: In 1212, children from all over Europe lead a crusade to free Jerusalem from Turkish authorities. Nicholas and Stephen use all their might to defeat the enemy.

Title: 358. Samoa, Queen of the Jungle
description: The adventurer Clint travels across Borneo with a bunch of rogues and geologists on the search for a diamond mine. Trouble with the natives begins when the diamonds are found because diamonds are holy stones to them.

Title: 359. Dead Men Don't Count
description: Two gunmen ride into a town with a plan to collect a large unearned bounty but are caught up in the local war for land caused by the impending arrival of the railroad.

Title: 360. White Comanche
description: Twin brothers, half white and half Comanche, take different paths that overlap with Johnny Moon getting blamed for Notah's violent acts until the final confrontation in Rio Hondo.
